{
  "intro": {
    "title": "Comparatives and Superlatives",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Comparatives",
        "content": "We use comparatives to compare two things. Add **-er** to short words:\n\n• tall → tall**er**\n• big → bigg**er** (double g)\n• easy → easi**er** (y → i)\n\nUse **than**: She is tall**er than** me."
      },
      {
        "title": "Long words: more",
        "content": "With long words we use **more**:\n• expensive → **more** expensive\n• interesting → **more** interesting"
      },
      {
        "title": "Superlatives",
        "content": "Superlatives = the best in a group. Add **-est** or use **the most**:\n\n• tall → the tall**est**\n• expensive → **the most** expensive\n• good → **the best** (irregular)\n• bad → **the worst** (irregular)"
      }
    ]
  },
  "check": {
